  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6818.63 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6810 (-50B) and max positive gamma at 6830 (+23B), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as spot hovers above the massive -50B gamma wall at 6810. The BREAKOUT regime with -103B total GEX means dealers will amplify any directional move—buying strength toward 6830 where they flip to selling, or aggressively buying any dip back toward the 6810-6815 negative gamma cluster. Watch for volatility compression if price gets pinned near 6830 (dealer selling zone) or explosive moves if we break below the 6810 wall where dealers become heavy buyers.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile swings between 6810-6830 with dealers amplifying any breakout from this range.",
